adptrNumber.name: adptrNumber
adptrNumber.description: The number of Cisco network adapter cards in the machine.

adptrTable.name: adptrTable
adptrTable.description: A list of adapter table entries. The number of entries is given by adptrNumber.

adptrEntry.name: adptrEntry
adptrEntry.description: An adapter table entry containing information about a Cisco network adapter card.

adptrIndex.name: adptrIndex
adptrIndex.description: A unique value for each Cisco adapter card in the machine. The value ranges between 1 and the value of adptrNumber. The value for each adapter card must remain constant at least from one re-initialization of the entity's network management system to the next re-initialization.

adptrSerialNumber.name: adptrSerialNumber
adptrSerialNumber.description: The serial number of the adapter card.

adptrHwHiVersion.name: adptrHwHiVersion
adptrHwHiVersion.description: The high part of the hardware version of the adapter card. For example, if the hardware version is 3.1, the value of adptrHwHiVersion is 3.

adptrHwLoVersion.name: adptrHwLoVersion
adptrHwLoVersion.description: The low part of the hardware version of the adapter card. For example, if the hardware version is 3.1, the value of adptrHwLoVersion is 1.

adptrFwHiVersion.name: adptrFwHiVersion
adptrFwHiVersion.description: The high part of the firmware version of the adapter card. For example, if the firmware version is 3.1, the value of adptrFwHiVersion is 3.

adptrFwLoVersion.name: adptrFwLoVersion
adptrFwLoVersion.description: The low part of the firmware version of the adapter card. For example, if the firmware version is 3.1, the value of adptrFwLoVersion is 1.

adptrSwHiVersion.name: adptrSwHiVersion
adptrSwHiVersion.description: The high part of the software version number. For example, if the software version is 3.1, the value of adptrSwHiVersion is 3.

adptrSwLoVersion.name: adptrSwLoVersion
adptrSwLoVersion.description: The low part of the software version number. For example, if the software version is 3.1, the value of adptrSwLoVersion is 1.

adptrStatus.name: adptrStatus
adptrStatus.description: The operational status of the adapter card. If the status is not ok(2), the value of adptrSelfTestResult gives more detailed information about the adapter card's failure condition(s).

adptrSelfTestResult.name: adptrSelfTestResult
adptrSelfTestResult.description: The result of the adapter card's self test. A zero indicates that the adapter passed all tests. Bits set in the result indicate error conditions.

adptrDriverHiVersion.name: adptrDriverHiVersion
adptrDriverHiVersion.description: The high part of the driver version number. For example, if the driver version is 3.1, the value of adptrDriverHiVersion is 3.

adptrDriverLoVersion.name: adptrDriverLoVersion
adptrDriverLoVersion.description: The low part of the driver version number. For example, if the driver version is 3.1, the value of adptrDriverLoVersion is 1.

adptrMediaType.name: adptrMediaType
adptrMediaType.description: The type of physical layer medium dependent interface on the adapter port(s).

adptrModel.name: adptrModel
adptrModel.description: The manufacturer's model number for the adapter.

adptrTrapReceiverTable.name: adptrTrapReceiverTable
adptrTrapReceiverTable.description: The adapter trap receiver table (0 to 10 entries). This table lists the addresses of Network Management Stations that should receive trap messages from this adapter when an exception condition occurs.

adptrTrapReceiverType.name: adptrTrapReceiverType
adptrTrapReceiverType.description: Setting this object to invalid(2) removes the corresponding entry from the adptrTrapReceiverTable. To add a new entry to the adptrTrapReceiverTable, set the adptrTrapReceiverAddr to an IpAddress which is not already in the table. The adptrTrapReceiverType for that entry is automatically set to other(1).

adptrTrapReceiverComm.name: adptrTrapReceiverComm
adptrTrapReceiverComm.description: Community string used for trap messages to this trap receiver.

adptrCommunityTable.name: adptrCommunityTable
adptrCommunityTable.description: The adapter community table (4 entries). This table lists community strings and their access levels. When an SNMP message is received by this adapter, the community string in the message is compared with this table to determine access rights of the sender.

adptrCommunityAccess.name: adptrCommunityAccess
adptrCommunityAccess.description: A value of readWriteAll(4) allows the community to read and write all objects in the MIB. A value of readWrite(3) allows the community to read and write all objects except the adptrCommunityTable, which it cannot access at all. A value of readOnly(2) allows the community to read all objects except the adptrCommunityTable. A value of other(1) allows the community no access.

adptrCommunityString.name: adptrCommunityString
adptrCommunityString.description: Configurable community string with access rights defined by the value of adptrCommunityAccess.

adptrMgmtType.name: adptrMgmtType
adptrMgmtType.description: The type of network management for the adapter.

adptrMgmtHiVersion.name: adptrMgmtHiVersion
adptrMgmtHiVersion.description: The high part of the network management version number. For example, if the network management version is 3.1, the value of adptrMgmtHiVersion is 3.

adptrMgmtLoVersion.name: adptrMgmtLoVersion
adptrMgmtLoVersion.description: The low part of the network management version number. For example, if the network management version is 3.1, the value of adptrMgmtLoVersion is 1.
